            To follow on , we witnessed a truly awful exhibition of refereeing, why are French refs so poor? No officials from France at this years World Cup, I believe , says it all. Overall a Derby match with plenty of niggly fouls, lots of endeavour from Nice and generally a poor standard of football. I was disappointed to see Toulalan substituted after which Monaco lost there shape. Yet another bizarre decision from the amateur coach. His replacement Dirar was dire!! Oh well it's Zenit on Wednesday.....

          • [ - ] FollowASM - member since 18-Aug-14

            Having been at yesterday's match I fear for us in our next two matches away at Zenit and PSG. Our lack of scoring opportunities are limited. The Russian owners were in attendance and they must be ruling the day when they sacked Mr Ranieri for being successful. 3 times we played Nice last season and 3 times we won. I admit our star players have gone, James being missed the most, after all Falcao did not play in any of the matches V Nice. You can not fault the owners decision to take the money for James and various others. What a great decision to sell Rivière to Newcastle, his hat trick last season was due to Falcao being double or triple marked. Yesterday after letting in a goal from a set piece , well executed by Nice, 2 players in our defensive wall who conveniently moved out of the way to let Eduardo's shot through, defensively naive by Monaco. Training ground stuff from Nice. Inspite of this Monaco had an overall 60% possession during the match. Post 2 to follow
